  "theoryOfChange": "Charity Water utilizes a 'monitoring and evaluation framework \u2013 called the MAP Framework' to understand the impact of funded projects, maximize effectiveness, and guide future funding priorities. This framework involves collecting data across a range of water, sanitation, and hygiene (WASH) indicators. The MAP Framework includes two primary data collection types: Annual Check-ins, which are household surveys conducted at the baseline and endline of a grant, and Post-Implementation Monitoring (PIM), a comprehensive assessment of past funded work performed every few years. The organization also details its approach to planning, choosing locations, finding appropriate technology, selecting partners, and ensuring sustainability of projects.",
